book

public boolean book(T t,
                    Time s,
                    Time e)
Books a given thing over a given span of time.

Parameters:
t - The the to be booked. This object must provide a "getBit" method which returns the bit which represents it in a BitSet.
s - The start time
e - The end time
Returns:
true if the booking was made. False otherwise.

isFree

public boolean isFree(T t,
                      Time s,
                      Time e)
Checks whether its is possible to book something within a given time range. This method simply does the prep work of checking: the real method which makes this decision is "amIReallyFree", which must be defined by extending children.

Parameters:
t - The thing that would otherwise be booked. This object must provide a "getBit" method which returns the bit to represent it in the BitSet.
s - The start time
e - The end time
Returns:
true if the booking could be made. False otherwise.

amIReallyFree

public abstract boolean amIReallyFree(T t,
                                      Time s,
                                      Time e,
                                      java.util.BitSet timeSlot,
                                      java.util.BitSet tSlot)
Makes the decision as to whether or not a given span of time can allow for a given object to be booked. Must be overridden by child classes.

Parameters:
t - The thing to be booked. This object must provide a "getBit" method which returns the bit to represent it in the BitSet.
s - The start time
e - The end time
timeSlot - BitSet representing all the already-booked bits in the given time range
tSlot - BitSet with the single bit of the "t" object asserted
Returns:
true if a booking could be made over this given time range. False otherwise.

roundTimeDown

public void roundTimeDown(Time t)
Truncates a time down to the previous half-hour. (7:55 becomes 7:30, 7:29 become 7:00, etc).

Parameters:
t - The time to round down.

roundTimeUp

public void roundTimeUp(Time t)
Rounds time up to the next half-hour. (7:01 becomes 7:30, 7:31 becomes 8:00, etc.).

Parameters:
t - Time to round up

computeSlots

protected int computeSlots(Time s,
                           Time e)
Computes the number of half hours there in a given time range. These half hours are given based on the times after they have been rounded down (start) and down (end) accordingly. So, if you wanted the number of half hours gave it the times 8:15 and 10:45, you'd get 6.

Parameters:
s - The start time
e - The end range
Returns:
the number of half hours it would take to go from "s" (rounded down according to the criteria of "roundTimeDown") to "e" (rounded up according to the criteria of "roundTimeUp").

computeStartSlot

Determines which of the 48 half-hour slots a given time will begin on

Parameters:
s - The time in question
Returns:
The half-hour slot "s" will start on
